The paper deals with the analysis of 3D shapes using convolutional neural networks designed specifically for triangular meshes. This makes it likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new network architecture that combines specialized convolution and pooling layers, which involves learning which edges to collapse, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves the use of neural networks for learning tasks, which makes it relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
